image is blueprint / template , to run container ..
the image is pulled from docker hub.
1. docker run -it ubuntu(image_name)  :- when this run '-it' help us to go under continer id . 
                                         i.e. its not return to local .but its goes under container interaction.  
---docker run (image name)            :-in this without 'it'its dont goes under the container id 
                                        i.e. its returns to local ..
// to see which container runnning :(when the container is start)
2.docker ps

// if the conatianer not start , to see alll con;tainer 
3. docker ps -a

// to check for images  (to see all images) 
4. docker images 

// to stop container not by manually
5. docker stop e80f1730d24b (container id/name)

// to start cotnainer 
6. docker start c3fb2e1b974 (container name / id)

// in particulaar conatiner, the will execute.
7. docker exec -it (continer id/name) _______(bash = to go under conatiner and open terminal)

// to delete a contianer 
8. docker rm c3fb2e1b974 (container name / id)


